During the weird part of the pandemic we filmed a short film at @capturedtattoo and I was so thrilled to be a part of it. It’s that time again. Another season, another set of pins. This time some cool throwbacks. I’ll have two more to add to this seasons set but for tonight’s @lafc match I will be hiding these around @bmostadium. 
For those who don’t know, a few years ago I started doing the pin treasure hunt at all home matches. It’s my way of giving back to such a vibrant and passionate community that I’m a part of. 
I hide them and take a picture of the general location. The rest is up to YOU. 
It’s easy. If you find one, post it! If you manage to get your hands on more than one of the same pin…then trade it with someone who might have the same. 
See ya later. #lafc #lafc3252

Been a few days since the @capturedtattoo 10yr anniversary party and the truth is I’ve been high on gratitude ever since. Trying to live in the moment is something we can all do more of. I could try and write something that tries to explain it all but I think I’ll just leave a whole lot of love right here to everyone who supports me, surprised me, those that flew from out of state, everyone who I see often, the people i barely see and the people who I wish I saw more for coming by on Saturday night. It was truly special and I wish it wasn’t as much of a blur as it is but i woke up Sunday knowing I am right where I need to be, and 100% surrounded by great, creative, interesting and funny and ridiculous people. How lucky? So proud of the crew at the shop. It’s never been better! Thank you Wife, thank you LIFE. #capturedtattoo #10years #tattooing

I celebrated being @skullysmith’s husband yesterday. Fifteen years to be exact. Nothing short of an honor. She changed my world and outlook and made me believe in magic. She is stunning inside and out and most days I wonder why she keeps me. I look at her sitting passenger in my car and my brain boils over. Her poise is unmatched. Her class is divine. Words will never be enough but I will continue to put her first and be the best me, for her, for us and keep believing in magic. Happy anniversary my darling. Here’s to forever.

Got an awesome surprise visit from @ericdressen yesterday! I had him sign the old tribal scorpion tattoo magic board that I had on ice for a few years too! Always loved that board and Eric too. Come see it hanging at @capturedtattoo sometime. #ericdressen #capturedtattoo

Played my first show with @18v_official at the incredible #forthechildren a few days ago. Felt so good to play heavy music again! Thanks for the pic @romoface and for all the support from friends leading up to the show. 18V and the entire OC scene were exceptionally welcoming and supportive to me and my band Day of Contempt when we first met on tour in Australia in 2002 and then after we relocated in 2004. Tragically our brother and bass player Mick Morris passed away in 2013 and the band never replaced him. It’s a privilege to be asked to make him proud.

Happy holidaze! Sending love to everyone! I hope you all had a beautiful Christmas and end of year holiday. Huge thank you to all my incredible clients and motivating friends that keep me going. Here I am in a freezing pool in the rain in Florida. It’s chill.
